    id: 2,
    title: "Training for the Ion Chromatography",
    content: "The training lecture on ion chromatography is about principles and operation of IC. It was on October 10, 2022, via Google Teams and attended by the UP Diliman Project Leader under the NICER program, Project 1, Dr. Pythias Espino and her project staff, together with LLDA representatives and the Project Leader of Project 2 under the NICER Lakes Program, Prof. Christian Paul P. de la Cruz and his project staff. The aim was to understand the basic uses and importance of IC in determining N or P nutrient contents in collected water samples.\r\n\r\nSubsequently, from October 11 to 12, 2022, a hands-on training on IC operation was held in the Center for Lakes Sustainable Development at the Laguna State Polytechnic University, Los Banos Campus, to learn more about the operations needed to run water samples and to know how to maintain and calibrate the said equipment.\r\n\r\nThe aforementioned activities helped the attendees learn how to run samples and calibrate the IC to achieve more accurate data sets for further data analysis.",
