    id: 6,
    title: "FGD for PRA under NICER Lake Project 2",
    content: "The FGD for PRA under NICER Lake Project 2 was held at Barangay San Pedro, Tiaong, Quezon, on April 4, 2022. The team assisted undergraduate students with their studies in order to inform the community about the activity's goals and benefits. While participating in the activity, the locals were indeed responsive and attentive. They were mindful that having a better understanding of the changes in their neighborhood could help them maintain the area's natural resources.\r\n\t\r\nThe team used timeline mapping, community-based mapping, causal mapping, resource mapping, and SWOT analysis as methodologies. The locals' responses were read aloud so that they might learn about the improvements and changes in the area. Following these approaches, the residents concluded that human activities such as population growth, fish cage expansion in the lake, and increased housing were contributing to the causes of various problems in their town.",
