    id: 9,
    title: "Selection of Tilanggit Project Beneficiaries in Brgy. Bayog, Los Baños, Laguna",
    content: "Last Sunday, August 28, 2022, staff of the Tilanggit Project went to the Brgy. Hall of Brgy. Bayog, Los Baños, Laguna, to conduct the selection of twenty (20) beneficiaries as part of the community-based rollout of the Tilanggit Project being implemented by the College of Fisheries, Laguna State Polytechnic University. The project staff, in collaboration with the barangay officials of Brgy. Bayog prepared the venue for the selection of beneficiaries. With the help of barangay personnel, the setting up of the sound system, laptop, and chairs was started at exactly 12:00 pm. Then, registration started at 12:30 pm. The program proper started at exactly 1:00 pm with an invocation, followed by the national anthem at 1:05 pm. After that, the host acknowledged the presence of the Brgy. officials who supported the event and the twenty-seven (27) attendees. Opening remarks, delivered by the chairperson of the Brgy. Bayog, Honorable Cristanto A. Tandang, marked the official start of the program. Then, Ruperto P. Olivares, Project Development Officer I, discussed the overview of the whole project. \r\n\r\nAfterwards, the discussion on how to answer the questionnaire or the shelter prioritization tool was discussed. During the discussion, a copy of the questionnaire was flashed into the projector. Alongside this, each attendee was given a questionnaire and asked to answer it truthfully. After answering the questionnaire, the Tilanggit Project staff distributed food, and while eating, the draw for prizes started. With the initiation of the project staff, twenty (20) kitchen wares were given away. Before the closing remarks, a photo op was done. Then, closing remarks were delivered. The program was officially adjourned at 3:30 pm. From 3:30 to 3:45 pm, cleaning of the venue was done. Following the cleaning, a brief discussion with barangay officials was held to discuss updates and the next step or future plans.",
