    id: 21,
    title: "Turn Over of Kitchen Materials",
    content: "A project of Laguna State Polytechnic University-Los Banos Campus funded by DOST-PCAARRD, under the implementation of the College of Fisheries (COF), called Tilanggit project or Community-based rollout of Tilanggit production technology; A resilience livelihood program for the vulnerable enterprise for vulnerable lakeshore family of Laguna Province conducted the turnover of kitchen materials on December 21, 2022 at Joey Lina Gym. Registration started at 8:00 am until 8:30 am. Then, the three (3) barangays were separated to have a short activity together with the UPLB students. After that, attendees went straight to the Joey Lina Gym to start the official turnover of kitchen materials ceremony. The program officially started at 10:00 am with opening remarks delivered by Mrs. Carolyn Marie Bonsol, staff member under the NICER project. Followed by a short discussion and sharing of what the beneficiaries learned from the short activity and the training they received from the Tilanggit project. Then, a short discussion of the program flow followed. \r\n\r\nThe first activity of the day began at precisely 10:30 am with a videoke challenge. The competition had seven (7) teams from the three barangays, MFARMC, UPLB students, and Tilanggit staff. After that, a trip to Jerusalem with the initiation of UPLB students was started, and eleven (11) people joined the game. The exchange of gifts took place from 11:20 am to 12:00 pm. Sixty-five (65) people participated in the activity. The lunch buffet was then opened at 12:00 pm. The winner of the videoke contest was announced while others were eating. After that, the attendees received all of the kitchen supplies, and a photo opportunity was held. Then, attendees were asked to answer a survey form. The program was formally over at 1:00 pm.",
