    id: 22,
    title: "Semi Annual Monitoring (DOST-PCIEERD)",
    content: "The Department of Science and Technology-–Philippine Council for Industry, Energy, and Emerging Technology Research and Development (DOST-PCIEERD), the monitoring agency, visited the Laguna State Polytechnic University, Los Baños Campus (implementing agency) on March 17, 2022, to conduct semi-annual monitoring for the project \"Predictive Estimation of Ecological Carrying Capacity: Tool for Sustainable Aquaculture Development in Selected Crater Lakes in the Province of Quezon\". The monitoring agency assessed the progress of the project's objectives as well as the problems encountered by the implementing agency. Ms. Liz Ahren C. Penaflor (Sr. SRS/PCIEERD), Ms. Charisma Delos Reyes (Project Assistant II/DOST), Ms. Laarni T. Piloton (Sr. SRS/PCIEERD), and Ms. Monica Blaise Saniel (Program Manager/DOST-S4CP) were the representatives of the monitoring agency. \r\n\r\nThe Center for Lake Sustainable Development (CLSD) building was also visited by the monitoring agency. The PMIS was discussed with the project staff of NICER Lake Project 2 to easily update the financial reports, work plans, and accomplished objectives of the project. The NICER Lakes staff that were being evaluated were Prof. Christian Paul Dela Cruz (Program Leader/Project 2/LSPU), Antone Kris Lim (Project Coordinator/LSPU), and Joselito S. Miranda (Project Staff, L1/LSPU). The program leader presented the accomplished activities and the expenditures of the project.",
